## Task: Add --version/-v to cloche, cloche-agent, and cloched version endpoint

Add version reporting to all three Cloche binaries.

## Version Format
Semver: major.minor.build, read from a version file (not ldflags).
- **Build**: increases on every compile
- **Minor**: backward-compatible API updates, feature additions
- **Major**: backward-incompatible changes, removing/deprecating APIs, incompatible gRPC API changes, removing cloche commands

## Requirements

### CLI (`cloche -v` / `cloche --version`)
- Prints its own CLI version
- Calls gRPC endpoint on running `cloched` to get daemon version
- Runs `docker run <project-image> cloche-agent -v` to get the project's agent version
- Displays all three: CLI, daemon, agent
- If daemon is unreachable or image doesn't exist, show `<unavailable>` for that component
- Version mismatches between components are **warnings**, not errors

### Daemon (`cloched -v`)
- Prints its own version standalone
- Exposes a gRPC `Version` endpoint that returns its version string

### Agent (`cloche-agent -v`)
- Prints its own version standalone

## Versioning policy for bead tickets
When creating bead tickets, assess whether the change requires a minor or major version bump. If so, tag the ticket so that the version bump is handled during the _finalize_ workflow while merging.

